    "description": {
      "en": {
        "provenance": "imported",
        "value": "In response to devastating earthquakes in Nepal, UNESCO participated in a detailed needs assessment to examine the full extent of the disaster and define a recovery strategy in the area of culture. \r\n\r\nHaving identified the most urgent needs, the purpose of this activity is to respond to the immediately, in particular for the emergency consolidation of monuments, temples and museums at the World Heritage Sites of Swayambu, Kathmandu Durbar Square Hanuman Dhoka, Patan, Bhaktapur and Changu Narayan. The funds will be used to hire workmen, experts and local entrepreneurs, as well as purchase equipment needed for the work."
      },
      "ne": null
